<p><b>Malaysian</b> or <b>Standard Malay</b> is the <a href="/wiki/Official_language" title="Official language">official language</a> of <a href="/wiki/Malaysia" title="Malaysia">Malaysia</a> and a standardized form of the <a href="/wiki/Malay_language" title="Malay language">Malay language</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Austronesian" title="Austronesian" class="mw-redirect">Austronesian</a> family. It is over 80% cognate with <a href="/wiki/Indonesian_language" title="Indonesian language">Indonesian</a> and is spoken natively by over 10 million people. As a second language, it is spoken by an estimated 18 million, mostly Malaysians from ethnic minorities.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
